body:
Hey,

the nginx template in the documentation has the following alias for static content:
```
location /static/ {
        alias /var/pretix/venv/lib/python3.5/site-packages/pretix/static.dist/;
        access_log off;
        expires 365d;
        add_header Cache-Control "public";
    }
```

which leads to a alot of file-not-found errors for people still using pyhton 3.4.

Changing the path to
```
location /static/ {
        alias /var/pretix/venv/lib/python3.4/site-packages/pretix/static.dist/;
        access_log off;
        expires 365d;
        add_header Cache-Control "public";
    }
```
obviously fixed the errors.

Maybe the documentation should mention this. OR did i overlook something?

Best regards.

See attached images, issue does not occur with Chrome. FF version is 48.0, haven't verified it on a different PC.

In attributes inherited from body, the inspector shows this:

```
{
    font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Helvetica, "Liberation", Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.42857;
    color: #333333;
}
```

Note the `line-height`. Setting it to `1.4` fixes the issue. 

`1.417` seems to be the largest working value, as an aside, which is incidentally the exact value set in `pretix/src/static/bootstrap/scss/bootstrap/_scaffolding.scss`. It _looks_ like a floating-point error, but nothing is ever simple:

Up until then, a quick fix would involve overriding either line-height or font-size in the `dashboard` class.

[This](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/25344493/discrepancy-in-line-height-computation-how-does-bootstrap-do-it) SO question indicates it's a font rendering issue - seeing as this is the second font issue (#167), maybe pretix should choose a font for recognition similar to its charming color. (A font that is rendered about the same in every browser.)

